## What do we analyze?

![](assets/soundwave.gif)

## What do we analyze?

![](assets/soundwave_example.jpg)

## What do we analyze?

- Speech rate (# of syllables/words per unit of time, including pauses)
- Articulation rate (excludes pauses)
- Ear-voice-span (*décalage*)

# State of the art in speech recording {.transition}

## Current topics

::: {.r-fit-text}

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- interpreting quality, cognitive load, and working memory
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- source language speed of delivery and interpreting quality
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- speech recording in training
  - for pedagogical and theoretical research
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- development of assessment tools for interpreting quality
  - 10 mins of audio can take up to 4 hours to assess!
:::
:::

:::

## Assessment tools via recording

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- accuracy is a good assessment tool, but other metrics can be used as well
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
- filled pauses
- ear-voice-span (décalage)
- fluency
:::

::: {.notes}
EVS shorter for professional vs non-professional interpreters with numbers.
WM & fluency.
:::

# Ethical issues in speech recording {.transition}

## Legal issues may arise when...

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- recorded individuals are unaware of such
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- recordings are used for purposes beyond those already specified
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- cloud-based speech-to-text conversion
:::
:::
  
::: {.notes}
cloud-based stt e.g., zoom: where are the recordings stored? are they deleted after? is the product stt deleted?
:::


## Data privacy

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
- anonymization
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- with the growing power of AI, is removing biographical info enough?
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- provide only *measures* from the recording instead of the recording itself
:::
:::

# Data measurements {.transition}

## Variables

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- can be central object of study (dependent)
  - e.g., influence of preparation time on pause length
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- can be factor influencing something else (independent)
  - e.g., influence of input speech rate on accuracy
:::
:::

## Data measurements

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- speech rate
  - best to use syllables, not words
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- décalage
  - measured in seconds
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- pauses
  - how to define what constitutes a 'pause'?
:::
:::

::: {.notes}
syllables better b/c langs differ in word length
décalage better w/ secs b/c of syllable/word length diffs b/w langs
notice that these are usually continuous variables, not categorical
:::

# Preprocessing of audio data {.transition}

## Transcription & alignment

![](assets/segmentation_alignment.png)

## Transcription & alignment

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- automatic speech recognition systems work poorly with more than one speaker
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- difficult to align source & target audios
:::
:::

# Finishing up {.transition}

## Review

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- speech recording is essential for making quantitative measures of speech
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- preprocessing the data is usually the lengthiest part
:::
:::

::: {.fragment .fade-up}
::: {.fragment .semi-fade-out}
- there are many ways of operationalizing variables of speech
:::
:::

